FT  04 JAN 92 / International Company News: NIC forecasts profit of Dollars
8m
NATIONAL Industrialisation Company (NIC) of Saudi Arabia expects net profits
of Dollars 8m for 1991, up 67 per cent on 1990, Reuter reports from Manama.
NIC, a joint stock company, was established in 1985 to set up petrochemical,
chemical, electrical and mechanical engineering projects in the kingdom. The
Riyadh-based company offered new shares to its 40,000 founder shareholders
worth SR300m (Dollars 80m) in November to double its paid-in capital to
SR600m. The offer was oversubscribed.
It was the third share offering last year by big Saudi companies.
